The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques for portrait relighting, which falls under the scope of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The relighting process involves manipulating the appearance of the subject, which is related to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
